<item>
            <title>[MGPG-41] Passphrase revealed when backspacing at prompt</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MGPG-41</link>
                <project id="12317521" key="MGPG">Maven GPG Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;At the &quot;GPG Passphrase&quot; prompt, if I hit the backspace key during the entry, the passphrase is printed in cleartext with one less character. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;GPG Passphrase: ******************^R
mysecretpasswor*^R
mysecretpasswo*^R
mysecretpassw*^R
mysecretpass*^R
mysecretpas*^R
mysecretpa*^R
mysecretp*^R
mysecret*^R
mysecre*^R
mysecr*^R
mysec*^R
myse*^R
mys*^R
my*^R
m*^R
*^R
*&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be fixed by replacing the &lt;tt&gt;MaskingThread&lt;/tt&gt; with Java 6&apos;s built-in password prompt (as the &lt;a href=&quot;http://grepcode.com/file/repository.jboss.org/maven2/org.apache.maven.plugins/maven-gpg-plugin/1.0-alpha-4/org/apache/maven/plugin/gpg/GpgSigner.java#217&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;code comment&lt;/a&gt; had suggested to do):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Console console = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.console();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ( console != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; )
{
    pass = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;( console.readPassword( &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;GPG Passphrase:  &quot;&lt;/span&gt; ) );
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
